Now, by the Pythagorean Theorem,

$$\begin{split} AC^2 &= AB^2 + BC^2 \\\ \Rightarrow \qquad AC^2 &= \frac{36}{100} \cdot BC^2 + BC^2 \\\ \Rightarrow \qquad AC^2 &= \frac{136}{100} \cdot BC^2 \\\ \Rightarrow \qquad AC &= \frac{\sqrt{136}}{\sqrt{100}} \cdot BC \\\ \Rightarrow \qquad AC &= \frac{\sqrt{68}}{10} \cdot BC . \end{split}$$

Therefore,

$$\tan{C} = \frac{AB}{AC} = \frac{AB}{\frac{\sqrt{68}}{10} \cdot BC} = \frac{10 AB}{\sqrt{68} \cdot BC} = \frac{10 \cdot \frac{6}{10} BC}{\sqrt{68} \cdot BC} = \frac{6}{\sqrt{68}} = \boxed{\frac{3\sqrt{68}}{68}} .$$
